Load Data¶

Load data obtained through Facebook's "Download your Information" feature. Each thread (group chats and direct messages) was combined into a single CSV file used here.

Explore¶

List out all columns, obfuscate thread and sender names, and create lists of top friends by count of messages.

In [26]:
name_key = pd.DataFrame(data.value_counts('sender_name')).reset_index().reset_index()
name_key.columns = ['sender_name_code', 'sender_name', 'sender_count']
name_key['sender_name_code'] = "Sender_" + name_key['sender_name_code'].astype('str')
data = pd.merge(data, name_key, on = 'sender_name', how = 'left')
In [49]:
thread_key = pd.DataFrame(data.value_counts('participants')).reset_index().reset_index()
thread_key.columns = ['participants_code', 'participants', 'participants_count']
thread_key['participants_code'] = "Thread_" + thread_key['participants_code'].astype('str')
data = pd.merge(data, thread_key, on = 'participants', how = 'left')
In [28]:
top5_friends = data.value_counts('sender_name').index.values[1:6] # Excludes myself
top10_senders = data.value_counts('sender_name').index.values[0:10] # Includes myself

Feature Engineering¶

Create additional features to enable deeper analysis.

In [31]:
data['Datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(data['timestamp_ms'], unit = 'ms')
data['Date'] = data['Datetime'].dt.date
In [32]:
import numpy as np
data['Text_length'] = data['content'].str.len()
data.loc[data['type'].isin(['Call', 'Subscribe', 'Unsubscribe']), 'Text_length'] = np.NaN
In [33]:
data.drop(['Unnamed: 0', 'timestamp_ms'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
In [34]:
data['emoji_happy'] = data['content'].str.contains(':)', regex = False, na = False)
data['emoji_sad'] = data['content'].str.contains(':(', regex = False, na = False)
data['emoji_xD'] = data['content'].str.contains('xD', regex = False, na = False)

In [58]:
graph_data = data.copy()
graph_data['Month'] = graph_data['Datetime'].values.astype('datetime64[M]')

graph_data = graph_data.groupby(['Month'])['content'].count()
graph_data = graph_data.reset_index()

graph_data
plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))
g = sns.lineplot(data = graph_data, x = 'Month', y = 'content')
g.set(title = 'Total Messages', ylabel = 'Messages')
